events.title: Service request created for camera lagging
events.description: A service request was created to address severe video lagging when viewing multiple IP cameras from the Control Application at 150 Park Row, New York.

keyFacts: A service request was filed on October 3, 2019, for severe video lagging issues with IP cameras at 150 Park Row, New York, NY 10007.
The issue was reported by someone named Hughwon and was assigned to technicians Jeff Cranor and Jeff McKenzie.
The problem was described as consistent and affecting all users, with power confirmed to the device but no spare device available on site.
The document appears to be a routine technical service ticket, not directly related to criminal activities or key figures in the Epstein case.
The location 150 Park Row, New York, is identified as the service location and billing address for the camera system.
